snippet: The prime ministers, David Cameron and Enda Kenny, traveled to Belfast to try to save Northern Ireland’s power-sharing government.
abstract: British Prime Min David Cameron and Irish Prime Min Enda Kenny arrive in Belfast to press rival parties in Northern Ireland to sustain their five-party coalition.
lead_paragraph: The prime ministers, David Cameron and Enda Kenny, traveled to Belfast to try to save Northern Ireland’s power-sharing government.

headline.main: British and Irish Leaders Hope to End Deadlock in Northern Ireland Talks
